'''''Adapis''''' is an extinct genus of [[Adapidae]] primate belonging to the [[Adapinae]] subfamily<ref>http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/5258/Adapis</ref> The genus was named by [[Georges Cuvier|Cuvier]] in 1822 and contains up to three species.<ref name="TPBDB">[http://paleodb.org/cgi-bin/bridge.pl?action=checkTaxonInfo&taxon_no=40750&is_real_user=1 The Paleobiology Database]</ref> Males were larger than females.<ref>{{Cite doi|10.1002/ajpa.1330560303}}</ref>

[[Image:Adapis parisiensis.jpg|thumb|left|''Adapis parisiensis'' skull and lower jaw at the Museum f<U+00FC>r Naturkunde, Berlin]] 
